-- STATS ChipPAC shares jump amid renewed takeover talk
-- By Rujun Shen and Anshuman Daga
-- Thu Jun 26, 2014 03:12AM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, June 26 (Reuters) - Shares in semiconductor firm STATS ChipPAC Ltd <STTS.SI> jumped as much as 16.7 percent on Thursday in strong volume on renewed talk on the sale of the company.

STATS ChipPAC, controlled by state investor Temasek Holdings [TEM.UL], said earlier in the month that it was in discussions with potential buyers. [ID:nL4N0OT1OP] An investor relations official declined to comment, and a company spokeswoman, based in the United States, could not be contacted immediately.